oward conformity and has enormous social benefits in reducing extremism, encouraging critical thinking, and protecting freedom itself. Sunstein concludes that while much of the time it is in the individual’s interest to follow the crowd, it is in the social interest for individuals to say and do what they think is best. A well-functioning democracy depends on it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aConformity. 0aLawxSocial aspects. 0aSocial influence. 0aSociological jurisprudence. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Social Psychology.2bisacsh  aBrexit.  aInternet.  abehavior.  acascades.  aconstitutional structures.  adeliberation.  ademocracy.  adissenter.  adiversity.  aeconomic.  aextremism.  afree speech.  agroup polarization.  agroups.  ainstitutions.  alaw.  alegal expression.  alegal institutions.  amovements.  anoncompliance.  apolarization.  apolitical institutions.  apolitical radicalism.  apressures.  asocial media.  asubcommunity.  aunanimous.1 aFrank, Robert H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479896585.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479896585423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479896585/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles